1. Download Positron installer from here: https://positron.posit.co/download.html
2. Upload installer to S3
3. Create EC2 with Ubuntu OS, us-east-2
4. Install AWS CLI
    sudo apt update
    sudo apt install -y unzip curl
    curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"
    unzip awscliv2.zip
    sudo ./aws/install
5. Copy Positron installer from S3
6. Install Positron
    sudo apt install ./Positron-2025.10.1-4-x64.deb


Workbench Setup
SSL config - https://docs.posit.co/ide/server-pro/admin/access_and_security/secure_sockets.html
openssl req -x509 -newkey rsa:4096 -sha256 -days 3650 -nodes   -keyout ${FILENAME}.key -out ${FILENAME}.crt   -subj "/CN=${CN}"   -extensions SAN   -config <(echo "[req]

aws configure export-credentials --format env
